/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:9","data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3"],"citation":"Curated evidence already covers retrieval evaluation, guardrails, structured outputs, and access control, but current representation surfaces them weakly."},{"signal":"Stakeholder translation and risk communication are curated but underrepresented","gap_type":"curated_but_underrepresented","why_it_matters":"The blueprint repeatedly values communication and stakeholder alignment, especially for architecture-heavy player-coach roles.","current_state":"Strong curated stakeholder-facing evidence exists in current-role achievements, yet the current summary and priority bullets emphasize system transformation more than translation, risk framing, and business alignment.","safe_interpretation":"The record supports technical-influence leadership claims without crossing into executive-business ownership.","recommended_action":"Pull one stakeholder-translation bullet into the top of the Seven.One narrative and use it to balance architecture with influence.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:250","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:266","data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3"],"citation":"Business education on technical debt, SME collaboration, and transparent risk communication are already curated but not sufficiently surfaced."},{"signal":"Enterprise integration story is fragmented across the representation layer","gap_type":"curated_but_underrepresented","why_it_matters":"The category values enterprise integration and stakeholder translation, especially where AI or platform capabilities must fit real operating environments.","current_state":"Integration evidence exists across current AI platform work, Samdock API design, and earlier systems-integration roles, but the current representation reads more as architecture plus retrieval tooling than enterprise integration leadership.","safe_interpretation":"Enterprise integration can be claimed safely when anchored to MCP tools, external integrations, scalable APIs, and legacy-bridging systems already in the record.","recommended_action":"Surface one integration-oriented bullet in the summary or top role bullets to connect AI platform work with enterprise-system adoption.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:78","data/master-cv/roles/05_osram.md:42","data/master-cv/roles/05_osram.md:90"],"citation":"Curated evidence supports external integrations, API design, and legacy-system bridging, but the master CV does not yet foreground that category-relevant thread."},{"signal":"Formal executive people-management ownership remains unsafe","gap_type":"unsupported_or_unsafe","why_it_matters":"This category does not require strong org-management evidence, but overstating it would still distort the record and create title-risk.","current_state":"The curated record supports mentoring, promotions, hiring-process leadership, and one 4-engineer team lead example, but it does not establish a sizeable reporting line, budget ownership, or sustained performance-management scope.","safe_interpretation":"Player-coach, mentoring, technical leadership, and selective hiring claims are safe; formal department leadership is not.","recommended_action":"Do not use Head of AI, VP of AI, Engineering Manager, or org-builder framing unless direct reporting-line evidence is added later.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:182","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:217","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:94"],"citation":"Current evidence shows coaching and hiring participation, not durable executive-management ownership."},{"signal":"Custom-model training, fine-tuning, and RLHF claims remain unsafe","gap_type":"unsupported_or_unsafe","why_it_matters":"The blueprint favors applied production AI integration; unsupported frontier-model claims would reduce credibility and are explicitly disallowed by the evidence store.","current_state":"The curated AI record shows retrieval, routing, evaluation, guardrails, semantic caching, and tool-calling architecture, but the do-not-claim ledger explicitly excludes fine-tuning, custom embedding training, and RLHF.","safe_interpretation":"Applied AI platform and quality-control claims are safe; model-training leadership is not.","recommended_action":"Keep AI framing bounded to platform architecture, retrieval quality, evaluation, guardrails, and gateway design.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/projects/commander4_skills.json:42","data/master-cv/projects/lantern_skills.json:49","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332"],"citation":"The evidence store explicitly blocks frontier-training claims while strongly supporting integration and evaluation work."},{"signal":"Broad EEA AI governance leadership remains unsafe despite narrow compliance evidence","gap_type":"unsupported_or_unsafe","why_it_matters":"The category label includes EEA, but the blueprint warns against implying region-wide compliance or regulated-industry authority without repeated proof.","current_state":"There is one curated GDPR/TCF compliance achievement plus per-silo content-policy guardrails, but the record does not show broad EEA AI governance ownership across organizations or programs.","safe_interpretation":"Narrow compliance and guardrail implementation claims are safe; region-wide AI governance leadership is not.","recommended_action":"Limit compliance language to documented GDPR/TCF and content-policy controls unless additional directly evidenced governance ownership is curated.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:106","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8"],"citation":"Existing compliance evidence is real but too narrow to support broad EEA governance-lead claims."}],"safe_claims_now":{"headline_safe":["Technical Lead / Software Architect for production AI and event-driven platforms.","Production AI platform architecture with delivery, reliability, evaluation, and guardrails.","Player-coach technical leadership across architecture, stakeholder alignment, and mentoring."],"profile_safe":["Architected a legacy AdTech platform transformation into event-driven AWS microservices, cutting incidents by 75% and sustaining 3 years of zero downtime.","Platform lead for an enterprise AI workflow platform serving 2,000 users and 42 plugins, with hybrid retrieval, LLM-as-judge reranking, semantic caching, structured outputs, and evaluation harnesses.","Hands-on architect who improves system health and delivery by combining observability, technical-debt strategy, and stakeholder education.","Mentored 10+ senior engineers, promoted 3 to lead positions, and scaled delivery across matrixed cross-functional teams without overstating formal org ownership."],"experience_safe":["Established architecture north stars, DDD standards, and event-driven design patterns that improved onboarding, velocity, and requirement alignment.","Built monitoring, alerting, and observability pipelines that improved incident detection, MTTR, and production debugging.","Designed AI quality controls including retrieval evaluation, guardrail profiles, per-silo policy enforcement, and schema-validated tool-calling outputs.","Delivered enterprise integration patterns through MCP tools, scalable APIs, and legacy-system bridges across multiple roles."],"leadership_safe":["Player-coach technical lead.","Mentor and design-review driver for senior engineers.","Cross-functional stakeholder translator on architecture, risk, and technical-debt tradeoffs.","Hiring-process contributor with interview and assessment design experience."],"unsafe_or_too_weak":["Head of AI, VP of AI, or Chief AI Officer.","Formal Engineering Manager with a sizeable reporting line.","Budget or P&L owner.","Primary model scientist for custom LLM training, fine-tuning, or RLHF.","Broad EEA AI governance lead beyond documented GDPR/TCF and content-policy controls.","Dedicated ML platform owner of full end-to-end MLOps across multiple programs."],"citations":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:88","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:106","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:163","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:182","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:217","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:9","data/master-cv/projects/commander4_skills.json:42","data/master-cv/projects/lantern_skills.json:49"]},"representation_diagnosis":{"well_represented_now":["Current summary already surfaces large-scale architecture modernization and delivery outcomes from the strongest Seven.One transformation story.","Project layer already surfaces meaningful AI platform depth through Commander-4 and Lantern, including retrieval, evaluation, semantic caching, and gateway design.","Skills representation is already richer on applied AI than the summary, with retrieval evaluation, LLM-as-judge, structured outputs, MCP tools, and gateway design present."],"underrepresented_now":["Architect/player-coach framing is weaker than the evidence base supports because the headline remains generic and the metadata does not yet surface upstream Technical Architect title evidence.","AI quality controls are underrepresented in the summary: evaluation, guardrails, structured outputs, and per-silo policy controls sit below the fold despite being category-differentiating.","Stakeholder translation, risk communication, and subject-matter influence are present in curated achievements but not prioritized in the current narrative.","Reliability proof exists, but the representation leans more on transformation than on ongoing operational excellence and observability leadership.","Enterprise integration is fragmented across projects and earlier roles instead of being presented as one continuous through-line into production AI."],"overstated_risk_now":["The generic headline 'Engineering Leader / Software Architect' can be read as broader formal management than the evidence clearly supports for this category.","The summary over-centers legacy modernization and understates current production-AI architecture, which can make the profile read more platform-modernization than AI-platform leadership.","Because the representation is proxy-derived, fit judgments on headline/summary balance remain provisional until a canonical master CV artifact exists."],"representation_priorities":["Make the headline architecture-forward and production-AI-specific without using executive AI titles.","Rebalance the summary so Commander-4 evaluation, guardrails, and platform-scale proof appear alongside legacy modernization.","Promote one stakeholder-translation bullet and one reliability/observability bullet into the top Seven.One narrative.","Cluster skills around architecture, observability, evaluation, guardrails, and integration before stack-specific tools."],"citations":["data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:163","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:250","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:266","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:7","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:9","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:7","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:9","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:10"]},"curation_priorities":[{"priority_rank":1,"action":"Promote claimable current-role title variants from the knowledge base into structured metadata so architect/player-coach framing becomes downstream-safe.","why_now":"Headline/title-family fit is one of the cleanest category gains available, and the evidence already appears claimable upstream.","target_files":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md","data/master-cv/role_metadata.json"],"source_refs":["docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:7","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:98","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:181","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:268","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:360"],"expected_category_impact":"High: strengthens safe Architect / Technical Lead framing and reduces pressure to use noisy executive titles.","citation":"Upstream STAR records explicitly support 'Lead Software Engineer / Technical Architect' and 'Technical Lead - Addressable TV'."},{"priority_rank":2,"action":"Curate richer structured provenance for current-role stakeholder and risk-communication evidence if the underlying STAR records contain more specific scope or outcomes than the current bullets expose.","why_now":"This market rewards stakeholder translation and player-coach influence; stronger provenance here would improve both curation completeness and representation quality.","target_files":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md","data/master-cv/role_metadata.json"],"source_refs":["docs/current/achievement-review-tracker.yaml:1051","docs/current/achievement-review-tracker.yaml:548","docs/current/achievement-review-index.md:117"],"expected_category_impact":"Me